{
  "texts": [
    "The datasets used included the training splits of MultiMedQA-namely MedQA, MedMCQA, Health-SearchQA, LiveQA and MedicationQA.",
    "We trained a 'unified' model, which is optimized for performance across all datasets in MultiMedQA using dataset mixture ratios (proportions of each dataset) reported in Extended Data Table 3.",
    "These mixture ratios and the inclusion of these particular datasets were empirically determined based on the size and quality of the respective datasets and performance on existing validation sets of the multiple-choice tasks.",
    "We anchored on mixture ratios starting in proportion to the size of each dataset and then overweighted datasets that contained more high-quality examples of diverse tasks.",
    "Unless otherwise specified, Med-PaLM 2 refers to this unified model."
  ]
}